dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government  Information Model - Administrative Areas Feature Class - School Districts
This layer contains school district boundary polygons and related attributes.  This layer is compiled by using the Auditor's annexation layer and is updated as new annexations are processed by the office.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: School District Boundaries

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model -Administrative Areas Feature Class - County Bndy
This layer contains county boundary polygons and related attributes for Franklin & surrounding counties.  This layer is reviewed periodically against using the Auditor's annexation layer and parcel layer and updates are made where needed.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: County Boundaries

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor UAV Flight Viewer - Map

This map depicts UAV Flights that have been conducted for Franklin County Auditor, within Franklin County limits, and attribute data that corresponds to these UAV surveys
dataset.title: UAV Flights

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - UAV Flights Dataset - UAV Flight Paths

This layer contains the flight paths of flown UAV surveys. According to the necessary survey, data is depicted as either a line or a polygon. This layer follows ESRI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to fit the needs of Franklin County Auditor and our customers. To download data, please see our direct download page.
dataset.title: UAV Flight Paths

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - UAV Flights Dataset - UAV Visual Extents

This layer contains boundaries and related attribute information of the approximate visual extents of individual UAV flights. Visual extents can and will overlap Multiple parcels. This layer follows ESRI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to fit the needs of Franklin County Auditor and our customers. To download this data, please see our direct download site.
dataset.title: UAV Visual Extents

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - UAV Flights Dataset - UAV Flight Locations

This layer contains UAV survey origin locations and attribute data associated with those locations. Locations are depicted as individual points. This data also includes the URL of the captured UAV imagery. The UAV Flight Locations layer follows ESRI's  Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers. to download this data, please see out direct download page.
dataset.title: UAV Flight Locations

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information - Property Foreclosures
This point layer contains Property Transaction where a Sheriffs Deed (SU) was filed as the latest instrument.    This layer is regenerated nightly, based on the previous days transactions.  Only the latest instrument is utilized in the creation of this layer.The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Property Foreclosures

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Parcel Publishing Feature Dataset - Tax Parcel Condo Unit
This layer contains parcel boundaries and related attributes for parcels within franklin County.  Condominium units are depicted as individual parcels.  Condominium Common Areas are identified with a polygon and simple attribute found in the Parcel ID field.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.  For other attribute schema and geometry types please see our direct download site.
dataset.title: Parcel Boundaries

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Elevation Dataset - Contours (Various)
This layer contains elevation contours derived from 2011 OSIP LiDAR Collection.  Twenty, Ten, Five, and Two foot contour intervals available at various mapping scales for Franklin County and the entire City of Columbus.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Contours (2')

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information - Property Sales Transactions
This point layer contains Property Sales Transaction by Land Use Type for the years 2014 thru present.  This layer is regenerated nightly, based on the previous days transactions and symbolized by year of sale.  The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Property Sales Transactions

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information - Registered Rental Properties 
This point layer contains properties that are registered with the Auditor's office as rental properties.   This is not an exhaustive list of rental properties, it is however all properties that are have an active rental registration on file with the Auditor's office.  This layer is regenerated on nightly based on the previous days transactions.  The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Registered Rental Properties

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information - Board of Revision Cases (2014-2017)
This point layer contains properties that have an active Board of Revision Case filing within the last 3 years (2014-2017).   This layer is regenerated on nightly based on the previous days transactions and case status is updated regularly.  The parcel centroid values are utilized to create these points with condominium units being spatially accurate.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.(2014 - 2017)
dataset.title: Board of Revision Cases

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Reference Data Feature Class -  Water Bodies
This layer contains polygon features of water bodies large enough to identify on 6 inch aerial photography.  This layer was originally derived from the 2011 OSIP LiDAR collection but is updated as part of the planametic (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office. This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Water Bodies

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Administrative Areas -  Historic Townships
This layer contains the historical township boundaries that previously made up Franklin County.  Many of these areas have since been incorporated.  This layer important when research historical deed information.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Historic Townships

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government  Information Model - Administrative Areas  - Municipal Boundaries
This layer contains municipal boundary polygons and related attributes.  This layer is compiled by using the Auditor's annexation layer and is updated as new annexations are processed by the office.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Municipal Boundaries

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Reference Data Feature Class -  Water (Stream Lines)
This layer contains line features of water and drainage not large enough to map in polygon form.  This layer was originally derived from the 2011 OSIP LiDAR collection but is updated as part of the planametic (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office. This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Creeks & Streams

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Reference Data Feature Class -  LBRS Centerlines
This street centerline file with potential address ranges and begin and end log points. A cooperative agreement among local agencies within Franklin County to maintain one road centerline file. The original file contains a 7 mile buffer outside of Franklin in order to provide complete coverage to cities that extend outside of the county boundary. However this service is limited to Franklin County only.  The Franklin County portion of the file is part of the ODOT/OGRIP statewide LBRS program and is periodically incorporated into their system.
dataset.title: Street Centerlines

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Reference Data -  Building Footprints 
This layer contains polygon features of buildings and other similar structures.  This layer was developed and is maintained as part of the planametic (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office. This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Building Footprints

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Reference Data -  Railroads
This layer contains line features of railroads (active and inactive).  This layer is derived from a number of sources including compilation from aerial photography and is part of the planametic (base map) mapping conducted by the Auditor's office. This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Railroads

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Parcel Publishing - Subdivisions & Condos
This layer contains subdivision and condominium boundaries and related attributes within Franklin County.  Common and Leagal Name attributes are provided for each polygon and these conform to parcel boundaries and right-of-way layers.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
dataset.title: Subdivision & Condominium Boundaries

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Parcel Publishing Feature Dataset - Tax Parcel Points
This layer contains parcel centroids and related attributes for parcels within franklin County.  Condominium units are depicted as individual units and are spatially correct.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers. For other attribute schema see our direct download site.
dataset.title: Parcel Points (Centroids)

dataset.description:
Parcel CSV Files (Tabular Information) - External Link
These files contain fields detailing property data, tax & value data, and CAMA attributes maintained by various divisions within the Auditor's office.  Documentation can be found in the documentation folder on the FTP site.  This data is provided from 1997-Present and is generally produced on a quarterly basis.
dataset.title: Parcel CSV Files

dataset.description:
Taxes & Payments, Property Values, Special Assessments (SA), Building, Land, Parcel Information, Permits etc. 
These CSV files contains fields detailing property data, tax & value data, and CAMA attributes maintained by various divisions within the Auditor's office and are more comprehensive then the parcel CSV file.  Documentation can be found in each folder on the FTP site.  This data is provided from 2014-Present and is generally produced on a quarterly basis.
dataset.title: Outside User Files

Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information - Appraisal Neighborhoods
This layer contains appraisal neighborhood boundaries and related attributes within Franklin County.  Appraisal Neighborhoods are defined by the appraisal department. This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.

dataset.description:
Franklin County Auditor - Local Government Information Model - Assessment Information Feature Class - Special Tax Districts (TIFs & CRAs)
This layer contains special district boundaries and related attributes for TIFs, SID, CRAs, and other special taxing districts.   These areas are generally defined by municipal governments but managed by the Auditor's office because of their impact on taxes.  This layer follows ERSI's Local Government Information Model (LGIM) schema and has been edited to meet the needs of the Franklin County Auditor and our customers.
